To find the intersection of (A x B) ∩ (B x A), we first need to find the Cartesian products A x B and B x A.

A x B = {(1, 2), (1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 2), (2, 3), (2, 4), (3, 2), (3, 3), (3, 4)}

B x A = {(2, 1), (2, 2), (2, 3), (3, 1), (3, 2), (3, 3), (4, 1), (4, 2), (4, 3)}

Now, we find the intersection of these two sets:

(A x B) ∩ (B x A) = {(2, 2), (2, 3), (3, 2), (3, 3)}

So, the intersection of (A x B) ∩ (B x A) is {(2, 2), (2, 3), (3, 2), (3, 3)}.
